[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, let us establish a firm understanding from the outset. Germany has no designs on Vienna or your Balkan territories - our expansion lies to the north and west. I propose we coordinate: I will move into Silesia and toward Denmark/Holland, while you push south and east. A German-Austrian axis is the natural order of Central Europe. I expect you to keep Russia occupied in Galicia. In return, I will not threaten Bohemia. Agree?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, Germany seeks peaceful relations in the east this opening season. I propose a simple arrangement: I will not move into Prussia aggressively, and you keep your forces focused southward toward Turkey and Austria. There is no need for conflict between our great nations in 1901. Let us both expand in our natural directions - you toward the Balkans and Black Sea, me toward Scandinavia and the Low Countries. A non-aggression understanding benefits us both.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I propose we divide the northern neutrals efficiently: Germany takes Denmark and Holland, England takes Norway. There is no need for competition in the North Sea this early. I am moving F KIE to Denmark and A BER toward Holland via the north. If you agree to this partition, we avoid a costly early conflict and can both focus on France, which threatens us both from the continent. What say you?'}]
