[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Greetings from Constantinople. Let us speak plainly: I have no interest in Sevastopol this year, and I propose we establish a clear division of the Black Sea region. I intend to move F ANK into BLA and A CON into BUL - both neutral centers that are rightfully in my sphere. I ask that you keep F SEV out of BLA and ARM, and in return I will not threaten your southern flank. A Turkish-Russian understanding benefits us both while the western powers squabble among themselves. What say you?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I write to propose a friendly understanding in the Balkans. I intend to take Bulgaria this spring - a natural Turkish interest. I have no designs on Serbia or Rumania, which I recognize as your sphere of expansion. Let us avoid any collision in the Balkans and instead focus our energies outward. I would welcome your thoughts on how we might coordinate to mutual advantage against common rivals.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, Turkey greets you. We are natural partners in the Mediterranean - I control the eastern straits, you the central sea lanes. I propose we establish a non-aggression understanding: I will not move fleets into the Aegean aggressively toward your interests, and I ask the same courtesy in return. Together we can ensure neither Austria nor Russia dominates the Balkans. I am open to deeper cooperation if you are interested.'}]
