[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Comrade, let us speak plainly. We both stand to gain from cooperation rather than conflict in the Black Sea region. I propose a simple arrangement: I will move F SEV to RUM this spring, leaving the Black Sea and Armenia untouched. In return, I ask that you keep your fleet in ANK and not contest the Black Sea. Romania is mine; Bulgaria and the Aegean are yours to pursue. A war between us only benefits Austria and the Western powers. Confirm your agreement and we can both expand freely.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I wish to establish clear boundaries between us from the start. I intend to move into Romania via Sevastopol - a neutral territory that rightfully falls within Russia's sphere. I have no designs on Galicia or your Balkan interests this year. In fact, I would welcome coordination against Turkey if you are interested - their expansion threatens us both. Let us avoid unnecessary friction and discuss how we might divide the Balkans to mutual advantage."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, Russia has no quarrel with you. I propose we establish a clear understanding: I will not move into Prussia or Silesia, and I ask that you respect the Baltic as a shared space. My fleet in St. Petersburg moves north toward Norway - no threat to you. I am focused entirely on the south and the Balkans. If you face pressure from France or England, know that Russia can be a reliable partner in the east. Let us keep our border quiet and both prosper.'}]
