[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I confirm our understanding: F TRI moves to ADR, A VEN stays or moves north, and we respect each other's home centers. I support your claim to Serbia and Romania. For my part, I will move F NAP to ION and aim for Greece and Tunis. Let us coordinate further in autumn - a strong Austro-Italian axis can dominate the Balkans and push back both Russia and Turkey."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I welcome your non-aggression proposal. My fleet moves south toward Tunis this year - I have no designs on the Aegean or your home centers. Greece is a point of potential friction; I suggest we discuss its fate openly rather than stumble into conflict. If Austria grows too strong in the Balkans, an Italian-Turkish understanding becomes even more valuable. Let us keep communication open.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, agreed - I have no interest in Iberia and will focus my energies eastward and southward. I will not move into Piedmont this spring. In return, keep your forces away from Tuscany and the Ligurian coast. A stable western border benefits us both enormously. I may need your diplomatic support against Austria later - let us keep this channel warm.'}]
