ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, your proposal suits Britain well. We agree: Germany takes Denmark and Holland, England takes Norway. I will move F EDI to NTH and F LON to ENG this spring, positioning for Norway and Belgium respectively. You keep your fleet out of NTH and we have no conflict. Let us both focus pressure on France - I'll threaten from the Channel while you push from the east. This Anglo-German understanding serves us both handsomely."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I appreciate your proposal, but I must be direct: I am moving F LON to ENG and F EDI to NTH this spring - these are essential defensive positions for Britain, not aggressive moves against you. I have no intention of taking Brest. However, I cannot promise to keep my fleets from the Channel entirely - that would leave Britain exposed. What I can promise is that Belgium is my target, not your home centers. If you focus south toward Spain and the Mediterranean as you suggest, we need not come into conflict. Let us watch Germany together.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I'm pleased to keep our lines open. My plan this spring: F EDI to NTH, F LON to ENG, A LVP to YOR - positioning for Norway and Belgium. I have no designs on your northern interests in Sweden or St. Petersburg. A coordinated Anglo-Russian pressure on Germany - should they overreach - would serve us both. I'd suggest you consider moving toward Scandinavia to secure Sweden while I take Norway; we can divide the north cleanly between us."}]
