[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your proposal is acceptable. I will move F ANK into BLA this spring - I need the Black Sea for access to Bulgaria and Romania eventually, but I have no intention of threatening Sevastopol this year. You take Romania, I take Bulgaria. This is a fair division. Keep F SEV away from BLA and ARM, and we have an understanding. Let us both grow at the expense of the neutrals and watch the western powers exhaust themselves.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I confirm our understanding. You take Serbia and Romania - I will not contest either. I am moving A CON to BUL this spring. Greece can wait; Bulgaria is my immediate priority. Let us both expand without collision and revisit coordination against Russia once we have consolidated. I appreciate your directness and look forward to a productive relationship.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your focus on Tunis suits me perfectly - that keeps you busy in the west while I secure Bulgaria and the Black Sea. I confirm our non-aggression understanding in the eastern Mediterranean. I have no designs on your interests, and I expect the same courtesy. Once we have both expanded, there may be opportunities for deeper cooperation against Austria or Russia - keep that in mind as the game develops.'}]
