[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, we are in agreement. F KIE moves to Denmark, A MUN moves to Burgundy to pressure France, and A BER moves to Silesia for eastern security. You take Norway and the North Sea - I have no fleet moving there. Belgium can be discussed once we've both secured our initial gains. France's proposal to leave Burgundy empty is convenient for them - I intend to occupy it and apply pressure. If you move against France from the sea, we can squeeze them from both sides. This is the natural Anglo-German arrangement."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, confirmed: Germany moves A MUN to Burgundy, F KIE to Denmark, A BER to Silesia. I am not threatening Bohemia - Silesia is purely defensive positioning against Russia. I expect you to move into Galicia to check Russia, and push toward Serbia and Rumania. We are natural partners - Central Europe must stand together. Keep Russia busy in the east and I will ensure France cannot threaten you from the west.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I appreciate your assurances. Germany moves A BER to Silesia - purely defensive, not toward Warsaw. F KIE goes to Denmark, A MUN to Burgundy. No German units threaten your western border. Focus your strength southward against Turkey and Austria in the Balkans - that is where Russia's destiny lies. The Baltic remains open to both of us. Let us keep this border quiet through 1901 and reassess from positions of strength."}]
