RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, your proposal is noted but unacceptable. You want BLA while I keep SEV idle - that gives you the Black Sea and leaves me exposed. Here is my final position: F SEV moves to RUM this spring. I will not enter BLA or ARM. You may take BUL via CON. But if your fleet enters BLA, I will treat it as an act of war and coordinate with Austria against you immediately. Romania is mine; the Aegean and eastern Med are yours. This is a fair division - take it.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I appreciate your clarity. Here is my concrete proposal: A WAR moves to GAL, F SEV moves to RUM. I am not asking you to support me into RUM - simply do not contest it. In return, I will support your moves into Serbia and the western Balkans. If Turkey moves aggressively into BUL or threatens your flank, we coordinate against them. Keep your A BUD focused on Serbia, not Romania, and we have no conflict. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, we are aligned. My F STP/SC moves to BOT this spring - positioning for Sweden eventually, no threat to you. A WAR moves south toward Galicia. I have no interest in Prussia or Silesia. I suggest you move aggressively into Denmark and the Low Countries - England will be your problem, not me. If England becomes too strong in the north, Russia can apply pressure from the Baltic in later years. Let us keep this channel open.'}]
