[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I am pleased we are aligned. To be specific: I will move F BRE to MAO this spring, heading south toward Spain — I will NOT move into the English Channel. I ask that you keep F LON out of the Channel as well, and instead push north into the North Sea. This keeps us both safe and expanding. Belgium is yours to take if you can reach it — I will not contest it this year. Let us build this understanding into a lasting partnership against German ambitions.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, I confirm my intentions: A MAR moves to Spain, A PAR moves to Burgundy only as a transit point — I will not threaten Munich. I expect the same restraint from you regarding Burgundy. Let us both grow strong this year and revisit our arrangement next season. A strong France and strong Germany together can manage England and Russia far better than if we exhaust ourselves fighting each other.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, agreed — I accept your non-aggression proposal. I will not move into Piedmont or Tuscany, and I expect you to stay clear of Marseilles and Spain. My fleet heads to the Mid-Atlantic, my army to Spain. Your path to Tunis and the Balkans is clear. Let us both grow in 1901 and revisit cooperation against Austria in 1902 — I may be able to support you diplomatically against Vienna if you keep me informed of your plans.'}]
