ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our spring arrangement worked perfectly - you secured Serbia, I'm well-positioned in the Ionian. This autumn I intend to move F ION - GRE as we discussed, claiming Greece for Italy. I'd appreciate your support or at minimum non-interference. In return, I remain committed to respecting Trieste and can support your continued expansion into the Balkans. I'm moving A TYR to hold or support your position - let me know if you need anything specific from me this turn."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, our non-aggression pact holds. I'm moving F ION toward Greece this autumn - I trust you'll keep your fleet in the Black Sea and army in Bulgaria without contesting the Aegean. In exchange, I have no designs on Constantinople or Smyrna. The eastern Mediterranean can be divided peacefully between us for now. Let's both grow and avoid unnecessary conflict."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, our non-aggression arrangement continues to serve us both well. I'm focused entirely on the eastern Mediterranean this autumn - Greece and Tunis are my targets. I have no interest in Marseilles or Spanish territory. I hope you're making good progress in the west against England or Germany. Let me know if there's any coordination that could benefit us both."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I trust we remain on good terms. My fleet in MAO will move to Portugal this fall — I have no designs on the Channel. I propose we coordinate against Germany: you take Belgium, I will pressure Munich from Burgundy if you support me diplomatically. Germany's silence last spring was suspicious and they are well-positioned in Silesia and Denmark. A Franco-British understanding now serves us both well before Germany grows too strong."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your silence last spring left me uncertain of your intentions. I moved to MAO rather than Burgundy — I have no hostile designs on you. Let us formalize a non-aggression pact: I stay out of Munich and Burgundy, you stay out of Belgium and Burgundy. I am focused entirely on Iberia this fall. I would rather have Germany as a partner than an enemy while England lurks in the Channel.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our pact holds and I am pleased with it. I am moving to Portugal this fall to secure my western flank. I trust you are pushing into the Balkans — Austria took Serbia and has a fleet in the Adriatic which threatens you directly. I would strongly encourage pressure on Trieste or Austria's southern flank. A weakened Austria benefits us both and keeps Russia honest."}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Kaiser, our arrangement proceeds well. I'm moving F NTH to Norway this fall - that's my prize secured. I expect you'll be taking Holland and consolidating Denmark. Belgium remains my target via F ENG - I'd appreciate you not contesting it. France is exposed with their army in Spain and fleet in MAO - if you push west from Burgundy, we can squeeze them nicely. What are your fall orders? Let's coordinate to ensure we don't accidentally clash."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I'm moving F NTH to Norway and F ENG toward Belgium this fall - no threat to your home centers whatsoever. Germany is the danger to watch - they have A SIL threatening your eastern flank and were pushing into Burgundy last spring. I'd suggest you consider whether MAO is the right position for your fleet or whether you need it closer to home. I'm happy to be a buffer against German aggression if you'll work with me on Belgium - perhaps we can agree I take BEL and you focus on Iberia and the Mediterranean?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I'm securing Norway this fall as planned - F NTH moves north. I trust you're consolidating your gains in the south and perhaps eyeing Sweden? I have no designs on Scandinavia beyond Norway. Keep me informed of what Germany is doing in the east - SIL is an aggressive position and I want to know if they're threatening you. A strong Russia keeps Germany honest, which serves us both."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I want to be direct with you: I now hold the Black Sea, which gives me leverage over both RUM and SEV. However, I have no interest in a costly war with you this early. I propose a practical arrangement: I will move A BUL to GRE this fall, leaving RUM entirely to you. In exchange, I expect you to keep F RUM out of BUL and A SEV away from ARM. We can both expand peacefully - you northward and westward, me southward. If you reject this and attempt to contest my position, I will push F BLA toward SEV and coordinate with Austria against you. The choice is yours, but cooperation benefits us both far more than conflict.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our arrangement holds well. I am moving A BUL to GRE this fall to secure that center, while F BLA holds the Black Sea. I am leaving RUM open for you to contest if you wish - your F ADR is well-positioned to support moves into the Balkans. I suggest we coordinate: if you want to push into RUM, I can support from BLA. Russia has F RUM there now, and together we can squeeze them. What are your intentions for this fall? I want to ensure our moves complement each other and we don't accidentally interfere."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our non-aggression understanding served us both well in spring. I am moving toward Greece this fall - I have no interest in the Ionian or Aegean as a threat to you. Your F ION is safe from me. I would ask that you keep F ION out of AEG and EAS this fall so we don't create unnecessary tension. In return, I will not contest Tunis or any western Mediterranean interests. Let us both expand in our respective directions without interference."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Excellent progress so far. My fleet is in DEN and I intend to move it to SWE this fall to secure that center. I'll also push A SIL toward WAR or PRU to threaten Russia, and A MUN toward HOL via RUH or BUR. I propose you move F NTH to support my fleet into SWE, or alternatively take NOR yourself while I take SWE - we split Scandinavia cleanly. On the western front, I'm moving to pressure France. Can you confirm you'll keep F ENG away from HOL so I can take it uncontested? Our arrangement is working well - let's coordinate the details."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Greetings. I note Austria bounced you out of Galicia in spring - a concerning move on their part. I am moving my units to secure DEN and SWE in the north, and positioning in Silesia purely defensively. I have no designs on Warsaw. However, I would suggest we both watch Austria carefully - they took Serbia and are building strength in the south. If you wish to press into Galicia this fall, I will not interfere and could even provide a distraction. What are your intentions this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Good progress in the Balkans - Serbia is yours. I am securing DEN and SWE in the north this fall. My army in Silesia remains positioned to support you if needed, or to threaten Russia's flank should you wish to coordinate a joint push into Galicia. Russia's fleet in BOT and army in SEV suggest they are spreading thin. I propose we maintain our cooperation - you press south and east, I handle the north and west. What are your fall orders looking like?"}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "You took the Black Sea as I expected - I won't pretend otherwise. I have F RUM and A SEV in the south. I propose we avoid direct conflict: I will not move into BLA or ARM this year, and you should not move into RUM or SEV. We both have more profitable directions to expand - you toward the Mediterranean, me toward Scandinavia and potentially the Balkans. If you push against me now, I will coordinate with AUT to crush you from both sides. If we maintain a cold peace, we both grow. What do you want from the Balkans specifically - BUL you already have, what about GRE and SER?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I note you took SER successfully - well done. I hold RUM and want to keep it. I propose a clear division: RUM and the Black Sea coast is mine, the western Balkans (SER, GRE, ALB) are yours. I have no interest in BUD or VIE, and I expect the same respect for my southern gains. Turkey is the common threat - F BLA gives them dangerous reach. I suggest we coordinate: if TUR moves aggressively, we respond together. I can pressure from RUM while you push from SER. What are your intentions toward BUL?'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, my F BOT is positioned to take SWE this fall. I propose: I take SWE, you take NWY - clean division of Scandinavia with no conflict. I will move F BOT to SWE and you can move into NWY unopposed. In return, I expect you to keep Germany occupied in the west so they don't threaten my northern flank. GER has A SIL which concerns me - if they push east I need to know you're pressing them from the west. Confirm you're moving on NWY and we have a deal."}]
