AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Good result in spring — your ION position is strong and TYR gives you BOH pressure if needed. My situation: A SER is sitting on an unowned center, F ADR is in position. I intend A SER to hold or move to GRE, F ADR to support or move toward ALB/ION. I want to coordinate on Greece — if you move F ION to GRE, I can support from ALB with F ADR via ALB, or I hold SER and we split the Balkans cleanly. What's your intended line this fall? I need to know whether you're taking GRE so I don't waste a move. Also: A TYR sitting adjacent to TRI and VIE is noted. I'm not alarmed yet, but I need it to move toward BOH or MUN this fall, not toward my centers. Confirm."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Russia took RUM with F SEV and has A WAR still in position — they're going to press both GAL and the Black Sea. You have F BLA which is the right counter. I'm holding SER and can move toward BUL or GRE if we coordinate. Proposal: you hold BUL and push CON toward SMY or support BLA against Russian pressure; I take GRE this fall with F ADR via ALB. We split the Balkans — BUL yours, GRE mine, RUM contested with Russia. If Russia tries to take BUL or push through RUM into SER, we both lose. Tell me your fall orders and I'll align mine."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "You have RUM and BOT — a strong spring. I have SER. The collision risk this fall is real: if you move F RUM toward BUL or SER, and I'm moving the same direction, we damage each other while TUR benefits. I'm proposing a clean line: RUM is yours, SER and GRE are mine. I will not contest RUM this fall. In exchange, keep A WAR out of GAL — I bounced you there in spring and I'll do it again if needed, but I'd rather we both use those units productively elsewhere. Confirm your fall intentions and I'll confirm mine."}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
