FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, agreed — you take Belgium, I focus on Iberia. My fleet moves to Portugal this fall, A SPA stays put to consolidate. I will move A PAR to Burgundy to signal pressure on Germany and keep them honest. Germany in Silesia with Denmark secured is a growing threat to both of us — if you take Belgium and I hold Burgundy, we have Germany squeezed from two sides. Let us build on this understanding into 1902.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I am moving to Portugal this fall — purely westward expansion. A PAR moves to Burgundy only as a defensive buffer against any English adventurism from Belgium. I have no designs on Munich. I propose we both stay out of each other's territory through 1902 and focus on our natural expansion zones. Your silence last spring made me nervous, but I am willing to trust you if you confirm this arrangement."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, Greece and Tunis are excellent targets — I fully support your eastern push. Austria's fleet in the Adriatic is a direct threat to you; I urge you to consider moving A APU to support a push toward Trieste or Greece while your fleet covers the Ionian. A weakened Austria opens the Balkans for you and keeps Russia from dominating the east unchallenged. Our western and eastern expansions complement each other perfectly — let us stay coordinated."}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Kaiser, confirmed: F NTH moves to Norway, F ENG moves to Belgium. I will NOT contest Holland - that's yours. On Sweden: Russia's F BOT is moving there this fall, so you may face a bounce if you try DEN-SWE. I'd suggest you consider whether to contest it or focus on Holland and the east. I'm keeping F ENG clear of HOL as promised. Let's both grow this fall and deal with France and Russia in 1902."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, we are aligned. My F NTH goes to Norway, F ENG goes to Belgium - no threat to you whatsoever. Germany is moving A MUN toward Holland and has A SIL threatening Russia - they are expanding aggressively on all fronts. Your fleet in MAO going to Portugal is sensible for Iberian consolidation. I suggest you keep A SPA positioned to defend and consider whether A PAR should move toward Burgundy to check German ambitions. A Franco-British understanding is exactly what I want - Germany must not be allowed to dominate the continent.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, confirmed - F NTH to Norway, you take Sweden with F BOT. Clean division, no conflict. Be aware Germany's F DEN may also attempt Sweden, so you may need to be decisive. I will keep pressure on Germany from the west - Belgium is my target this fall which will occupy German attention. Watch A SIL carefully; if they push toward Warsaw I want to know immediately so we can coordinate a response. Our arrangement stands."}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, confirmed: F ION moves to GRE this fall - that center is mine. A TYR will move to BOH as you requested, not toward your home centers. I need your F ADR to stay out of the Ionian and not interfere with my Greek move. If A SER moves to GRE we will clash - please hold SER or move it elsewhere. I'm honoring our arrangement and expect the same. Let's both build this winter and discuss coordinated expansion in 1902."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I hear your request about AEG and EAS - I will keep F ION out of AEG this fall, moving instead to GRE directly from ION. This should not threaten you. However, I must be clear: Greece is Italy's target this autumn. If A BUL moves to GRE we will have a serious problem. Hold BUL and we remain at peace. I have no interest in your home centers and will honor our non-aggression fully if you respect my claim to Greece."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, Austria's F ADR is a concern but I have it managed diplomatically for now - I'm taking Greece this fall and building. Austria is useful as a buffer against Russia and Turkey for the moment, but I agree they cannot be allowed to dominate the Balkans unchecked. Once I have Greece and Tunis secured, I'll be in position to pressure Austria's southern flank. Let's stay coordinated - keep me informed of your western progress and I'll do the same from the south."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Agreed - cold peace it is. I will keep F RUM stationary and A SEV out of ARM this fall. You move A BUL to GRE, I take SWE in the north. We both grow without bleeding each other. But understand this clearly: if F BLA moves toward SEV or RUM at any point, I will treat it as an act of war and coordinate with AUT immediately. Honor this arrangement and we can discuss longer-term cooperation against whoever grows too strong in the west.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, we have a deal. RUM is mine, SER and GRE are yours - I will not contest them. A WAR will not move to GAL this fall; I am moving it north toward LVN to support my Scandinavian push. F RUM will hold to secure the center. TUR is moving A BUL to GRE which means they're expanding south - watch that carefully, as GRE borders your sphere. If TUR overextends, we should be ready to act together. For now, let us both consolidate and grow without collision."}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, confirmed - F BOT moves to SWE this fall, you take NWY. Clean split, no conflict. On Germany: A SIL is positioned to threaten either WAR or GAL. I am watching it carefully. If GER pushes east, I will need you pressing hard from the west - make sure they feel pressure in BUR and DEN. A Germany squeezed between us cannot threaten either of us. Let us stay coordinated and communicate regularly as the board develops.'}]
