[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Greetings from Constantinople. I want to confirm our cold peace arrangement remains intact - F BLA stays in the Black Sea, I have no designs on SEV or RUM, and I expect A SEV to remain out of ARM. Turkey's expansion is westward toward Greece and the Balkans, not northward into Russian territory. Let us maintain this understanding and both prosper."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, our cooperation continues to serve us both well. I am moving A BUL toward Greece this season to claim that center - Italy appears to be eyeing it as well so timing is critical. I would ask that you consider supporting my move into Greece from Serbia if possible, or at minimum hold your positions to avoid any confusion. In return, I have no designs on Serbian territory - that remains yours. Let us coordinate to keep Italy from dominating the Mediterranean.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I propose we avoid a costly bounce in Greece. I am moving A BUL to Greece this season - if you are also targeting Greece with your Ionian fleet, we will both waste our moves. I suggest you redirect F TUN or your Ionian fleet toward the western Mediterranean where France is vulnerable, and I will take Greece. This way we both gain centers rather than canceling each other out. What say you?'}]
