--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Spring 1902. I want to coordinate cleanly. My plan: F ALB - GRE (taking the uncontested center), A SER supports F ALB into GRE, A BUD holds or moves to RUM depending on what Turkey does. I need confirmation you are keeping A BOH out of my home centers — VIE and TRI must stay clear. In return I will not contest VEN or TYR. If you want to push into the Aegean, GRE is yours after I take it this turn — I can move on to BUL or RUM. What are your actual orders this phase?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Spring 1902. I have no hostile intent toward you this phase — my focus is GRE, not RUM or BUL. I propose we avoid collision: I take GRE with F ALB, you hold BUL and RUM. If Russia moves on SEV or threatens your north, I can apply pressure from the Balkans to keep them occupied. What is your read on Russia's intentions this spring, and what are you planning?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Spring 1902. I kept my word last fall — A SER held, I did not contest RUM. I am moving F ALB toward GRE this spring and have no designs on RUM or GAL this phase. I want to keep our border quiet. What are your intentions in Galicia and the Black Sea? If you are pressing Turkey, I have no objection — a weaker Turkey suits us both.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Good work last year - we both secured our targets. Now let's coordinate for 1902. I'm planning F NWY -> SWE to take that center (Russia and Germany both failed to grab it, so it's ripe). F BEL -> HOL would give me Holland while you consolidate. I'd suggest you push A PRU -> LVN or A RUH -> BEL to support our positions. France has 5 centers now and is growing - we should consider coordinating pressure on them. What are your intentions this spring?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, we've maintained our understanding well. I'm moving to consolidate in Scandinavia this season - F NWY toward SWE. I have no designs on your home centers. Germany is the real threat on the continent - A PRU threatens Russia, and they'll be looking to expand west eventually. I'd suggest you keep A BUR positioned to deter German aggression. What are your plans for 1902? I want to ensure we're not working at cross-purposes."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the SWE bounce last fall was unfortunate for both of us - Germany still doesn't hold it, which is good. I'm moving F NWY -> SWE this spring to claim it before Germany can. I'd ask you not to contest this - SWE is more naturally in my sphere, and I'll support your interests elsewhere. Germany's A PRU threatens your LVN - I'd recommend you reinforce that flank. Let's keep our understanding strong and focus on containing German expansion."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, our arrangement continues to serve us both well. I intend to move F POR to MAO this season to consolidate my Atlantic position, while A BUR holds to keep pressure on Germany's western flank. I trust you are consolidating BEL and NWY — Germany's silence worries me. A RUH sitting next to BEL is a threat to you. I would strongly suggest we coordinate: if you move F BEL to support a push toward HOL or threaten RUH, I can support from BUR. Germany must not be allowed to grow unchecked. What are your intentions this season?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I want to be direct with you: A BUR will hold this season as a defensive buffer — I have no intention of moving into MUN or RUH. However, I am watching England carefully. F BEL sitting on your doorstep is a genuine threat to you, and I think we both know England's ambitions in the Low Countries are dangerous. If you are willing to coordinate against English expansion, I am open to discussing it. A RUH could move to BEL with support from BUR — that would remove England's foothold on the continent. Think about it."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, our non-aggression holds and I see no reason to change that. I note you have A BOH in a strong position — Austria looks vulnerable with only three units spread thin. If you push into Vienna or Trieste, I will not interfere and will cheer you on. I am focused entirely on the west — England and Germany are my concerns. Let us keep our arrangement clean and both expand in our respective directions.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation in the north is clear: F BOT moves to SWE this spring. GER's F DEN is a problem for both of us - they're contesting SWE and sitting in PRU threatening my LVN. I propose we coordinate: I take SWE with F BOT, you hold NWY and consider pressure on DEN from BEL or NTH. A LVN can move to PRU if you can support from somewhere, or I can use it to reinforce STP. What are your intentions regarding GER? I'm open to a joint squeeze on them if you're willing to commit."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'I want to maintain our cold peace in the south. F RUM will not move to BUL, and A SEV will not enter ARM - I honor my commitments. However, I expect the same from you: F BLA must not threaten SEV or RUM. I am focused entirely on the north this season. If you are willing to discuss a formal partition of the Balkans - you take GRE and BUL, I hold RUM - we can avoid a costly war that benefits only AUT and ITA. What are your intentions this spring?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'I intend to keep A LVN in the north and focus on Sweden this season - no moves toward GAL. F RUM holds as agreed. I want to flag that ITA has A BOH sitting on your doorstep and F TUN in the Mediterranean - they are quietly building strength while we watch each other. A Russo-Austrian understanding against Italian expansion in the Balkans could be mutually beneficial. What are your plans for SER and the Adriatic this spring?'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Our cooperation continues to serve us both well. I have A BOH positioned perfectly - I intend to move it to VIE this spring, which I offer to you as a staging point if you wish, or I can push toward MUN to pressure Germany. More importantly, I want to coordinate against Turkey - they now hold RUM and BUL and are growing dangerous. I propose we work together: I'll build a fleet in Naples and push into the eastern Mediterranean while you press on BUL from Serbia. What are your intentions this spring? I want to ensure we don't accidentally clash."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I want to be direct with you: I took Tunis last autumn and you took Greece - we both got our builds without bouncing each other, which was the sensible outcome. However, I'm concerned about your rapid growth - RUM, BUL, GRE is a very strong position. I propose we establish a clear line: you stay out of ION and I stay out of AEG. I have no immediate designs on your centers, but I need assurance you won't push into the western Mediterranean. Can we agree on a non-aggression pact for 1902?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I have A BOH adjacent to Munich right now. I have no hostile intentions toward you - I'm focused on the Mediterranean. However, I want to propose a deal: if you support my A BOH into VIE (Austria's capital), I will immediately move out of Bohemia and leave your western flank secure. Austria is growing with 4 centers and needs to be checked. Alternatively, if you prefer I simply vacate BOH toward TYR, I can do that too. What would be most useful to you this spring?"}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Excellent progress last year - you secured NOR and BEL, I have DEN. Now let's coordinate for S1902: I intend to move F DEN -> SWE and A RUH -> HOL, which gives us both strong positions. I need you to keep F BEL where it is or move it to support my HOL grab if possible - specifically, F BEL can support A RUH -> HOL. In return, I will not contest NTH or threaten your northern position. France is the common enemy here - A BUR threatens both of us. Shall we coordinate a joint squeeze on France? I can push from BUR/HOL while you press from BEL."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'A word of warning from a friendly neighbor: I have intelligence suggesting Austria and Turkey may be coordinating against you in the south. My A PRU is purely defensive - I have no designs on WAR or LVN. I am focused entirely westward toward HOL and France. I would encourage you to press hard into Galicia and keep Austria occupied - it serves both our interests to keep Vienna weak. I propose we formalize non-aggression: you stay east of the Silesia-Prussia line, I stay west of it. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "I want to maintain our understanding of mutual restraint. My moves this spring are directed north - F DEN toward Sweden, A RUH toward Holland. I have no intention of moving into Burgundy. However, I must warn you: England's F BEL is a direct threat to you, and their A LVP could reinforce. I suggest you consider moving A BUR to defend Paris or press toward Belgium - England is your real enemy here, not Germany. I am willing to coordinate against England if you are interested in reclaiming BEL."}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
