TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, congratulations on securing Greece - well played. I am holding my position in BUL and RUM this fall, consolidating our shared Balkan sphere. I want to discuss our next moves: ITA has A BOH threatening your northern flank and F ION in the Ionian. With ITA at 4 centers and growing, they are becoming a real threat to both of us. I propose we coordinate against ITA - I can push F RUM toward the Adriatic eventually while you press from the north. What are your intentions this fall? I will hold BUL and RUM to maintain our buffer.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, the ION/AEG non-aggression line holds on my end - F RUM stays in the Black Sea region and I have no designs on your Mediterranean position. However, I note you have A BOH pressing into Austrian territory. Austria is my current partner in the Balkans, so I want to understand your intentions. If you are planning to expand northward into Germany, I have no objection. But if you move against Austria aggressively, I will need to reassess our arrangement. What are your plans this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I want to maintain the cold peace between us. F RUM stays where it is - I have no intention of pushing further north this season. A ARM is noted near ANK; I trust you will keep that army focused westward rather than threatening my home centers. I am consolidating in the Balkans and have no designs on SEV at this time. Let us both focus on our respective threats - you have Germany pressing from the west, and I have Austria to manage. A stable southern front benefits us both.'}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "My friend, the situation is developing well. Germany remains the primary threat to both of us — their A SIL and A RUH are positioned aggressively, and Italy's A BOH in the east is a wild card. I intend to press A BUR toward MUN this fall, striking at the heart of German power. I ask that you hold F BEL firm and consider supporting my move into MUN, or alternatively push toward HOL to stretch Germany thin. Together we can crack Germany open. What are your intentions this season?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, I have been watching the board carefully. Italy has A BOH sitting on your doorstep — that is a serious threat to MUN that you cannot ignore. I am willing to coordinate with you against Italy if you are interested. My A BUR can support your defense of MUN, or we can discuss other arrangements. England is also growing fat with BEL and NWY — perhaps we should discuss how to check their expansion together. What are your plans this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your A BOH is excellently placed — MUN is ripe for the taking. I intend to move A BUR to MUN this fall as well, so we may bounce each other unless we coordinate. I propose you support my A BUR into MUN, and in exchange I will support your future moves southward and stay entirely out of Piedmont and Tuscany. Alternatively, if you prefer to take MUN yourself, tell me and I will find another target. Let us not waste this opportunity by working at cross-purposes.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, my army in BOH bounced off MUN last spring as you saw - Germany held firm. I'm now considering my options carefully. I want to maintain our working relationship, but I need to expand somewhere. I propose we coordinate against Turkey: I move F ION to GRE (you support or stand aside), and we split the Balkans between us. TUR has 5 centers and is growing dangerous. What are your thoughts on a joint anti-Turkish push?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, my BOH army bounced off MUN last spring - your unit in RUH was the problem. I'm still interested in coordinating against Austria. If you move A SIL to support me into VIE, I'll move A BOH - VIE this fall. That gives you a free hand in the north while I crack open Austria's heartland. Are you willing to commit to this? I need to know your actual orders, not just intentions."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, you now hold 5 centers including GRE - congratulations. I want to be direct: I need to expand and GRE is the obvious target for my fleet. Rather than fight over it, let's discuss a division of spoils. If you vacate GRE and focus on RUS (SEV is ripe for you), I'll support your northern push and stay out of AEG. We can both grow without fighting each other. What do you say?"}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation in the north is clear: F BOT moves to SWE this fall. I need your confirmation that F NWY will NOT move to SWE - if you hold NWY or move elsewhere, we both profit. Sweden goes to Russia, Norway stays yours. Additionally, I want to coordinate against Germany - GER's F DEN and A SIL are threats to both of us. If you can pressure DEN from NWY, I can threaten from the Baltic. Let's squeeze GER together and divide the spoils. Confirm your moves."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, Turkey now holds 5 centers to my 4 - this imbalance threatens both of us. TUR has F RUM on your doorstep and A BUL adjacent to your holdings. I propose we coordinate: I will move A ARM to pressure ANK while you consider whether TUR's expansion into GRE serves your interests. A strong Turkey is a danger to Vienna as much as Moscow. I am moving to contain them this fall - I would welcome Austrian cooperation or at minimum neutrality as I push back against TUR's gains."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, our cold peace has served us both, but I must be direct: your 5-center position while I hold only 4 creates an imbalance I cannot ignore. I am moving A ARM this fall - not to threaten you, but to position for future options. I propose we formalize a genuine non-aggression pact: F RUM stays out of SEV, A ARM stays out of ANK, and we both focus expansion elsewhere. I can grow north toward Sweden; you can consolidate in the Balkans. Respond with your intentions.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "The SWE bounce last spring was unfortunate for me - Germany and Russia both blocked my path. I'm now positioned in NWY and need to decide my next move carefully. I want to coordinate with you against Germany this fall. I propose: I move F NWY->SWE to pressure Germany's northern flank, while you push A BUR toward MUN or hold pressure on RUH. Germany has 4 centers and is the primary continental threat. If we squeeze them from both sides, we can limit their growth. What are your intentions for F1902? I want to ensure we're aligned before committing orders."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I see you're in DEN with your fleet and have strong army positions. I'm moving F NWY->SWE this fall to secure that center - I hope you're not planning DEN->SWE as we'd simply bounce again and waste both our moves. I suggest you hold DEN or move elsewhere, and I'll take SWE cleanly. In return, I have no designs on DEN or KIE, and I'm willing to coordinate against France if you're interested - their MAO fleet and BUR army are concerning. What are your plans this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I'm moving F NWY->SWE this fall as we discussed - you graciously conceded that center to me last spring. I appreciate the cooperation. I want to maintain our friendly understanding: I have no interest in STP or your northern territories. In return, I'd ask you keep pressure on Germany from the east - your A WAR and F BOT are well-positioned. Turkey is growing with 5 centers now which should concern you more than anything I'm doing in Scandinavia. Let's stay coordinated."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Your A BOH sitting in Bohemia is a direct threat to Munich, and I want to be clear: I will not tolerate it. Last spring you tried to take MUN and I blocked you. This fall, A SIL is positioned to move into BOH or support an attack on you from multiple directions. However, I am willing to offer you a genuine arrangement: move A BOH south toward Vienna or Galicia - away from my territory - and I will support your expansion into Austria. I have no interest in Italy's southern ambitions. But if BOH stays pointed at MUN, I will treat you as an enemy and act accordingly. Your choice."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'England is the common threat between us. They hold BEL and NWY, they want HOL, and they are positioning to dominate the north. I propose we coordinate: I will move A RUH into HOL this fall, denying England that center. If you can pressure BEL from BUR, we can squeeze England out of the continent entirely. I am not your enemy - I want to expand east and north, not into France. Let us formalize this anti-English arrangement now. What can you offer in terms of pressure on BEL?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Sweden remains unclaimed and both our fleets are positioned to contest it. Rather than bounce each other again, let us make a deal: I take SWE with F DEN this fall, and in exchange I will support your expansion southward against Turkey or Austria - whichever you prefer. I have no designs on Warsaw or your eastern territories. My focus is westward against England and France. A German-Russian understanding benefits us both - you dominate the east, I dominate the west. Confirm your intentions regarding SWE so we can avoid another pointless bounce.'}]
