AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey — I took GRE as agreed, you held BUL. Clean execution. Now we need to talk about the next phase. I have F GRE, A SER, A BUD. You have F RUM, A BUL, A CON. Italy has F ION sitting between us — that fleet is a problem for both of us. I propose: I move F GRE to AEG or support you into a position that pressures CON's neighbors, while you and I coordinate to squeeze Italy out of the Ionian. Alternatively, if you want to consolidate, I am willing to hold my southern line stable while you push north against Russia. What is your priority this fall — Italy or Russia?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy — I see A BOH is still on my doorstep and F ION is now in the Aegean theater. I took GRE this spring as planned. I want to be direct: I have no interest in fighting you if we can agree on a clean division. My focus is the Balkans and Turkey long-term. If you are genuinely moving against Germany via MUN, I can support that direction and keep my units away from BOH and TYR. But if A BOH moves toward VIE or TRI this fall, I will treat it as war and coordinate accordingly with Russia and Germany. Tell me your actual intentions for F1902 and I will tell you mine.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia — I am at 5 centers now with GRE secured. Italy has A BOH adjacent to my home centers and F ION in the south — they are the growing threat. I want to coordinate: if you can keep pressure on Italy from the north (GAL toward BOH, or WAR positioning), I will push from the south. Turkey is also a concern at 5 centers, but Italy's positioning is the immediate problem. What are your intentions for F1902 — are you moving against Italy, Turkey, or consolidating?"}]
