GER
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Final offer: Move A BOH to VIE this fall and I will order A SIL to support your move into Vienna. This is a genuine commitment - I want Austria cracked open and you are the tool to do it. If BOH stays or moves toward MUN, A SIL moves into BOH and you will be fighting on two fronts. I am issuing my orders now. Make the right choice.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Agreed on the English threat. My orders this fall: A RUH moves to HOL, denying England that center. I need you to pressure BEL from BUR - even a move that threatens BEL forces England to defend rather than expand. If you can commit A BUR toward BEL, we split England's attention and I secure HOL. This is the moment to act - England is overextended with NWY and BEL both. Confirm you will press BEL."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'I am moving F DEN to SWE this fall - I need that center and I will not yield it. If you move F BOT to SWE we bounce again and neither of us gains anything. Better you move BOT toward Finland or the Baltic and let me have SWE cleanly. In return, I will stay out of your northern affairs entirely and support your push against Turkey or Austria diplomatically. Another bounce serves no one - let us be rational about this.'}]
