ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I hear you clearly. My actual intention this fall: A BOH moves to MUN (away from your centers entirely), F ION moves to GRE to contest it. I have no orders pointing at VIE or TRI. I want the Balkans split between us with Turkey as our shared enemy - you keep SER/BUD/VIE/TRI, I take GRE and we coordinate against TUR together. If you support F ION into GRE or simply stand aside, we can formalize this anti-Turkish alliance. I need you to not support GRE against me this fall.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I've reconsidered. You're right that BOH pointed at MUN creates unnecessary conflict between us. I'm moving A BOH to VIE this fall - directly into Austria's heartland. If you move A SIL to support me into VIE, we crack Austria open together. You get a free hand in the north and I expand south. This is a genuine offer - commit your SIL to support BOH-VIE and we both profit. Austria is the real threat to both of us right now."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, I'll be direct: I'm moving F ION to GRE this fall. Austria has it and I need it. I'm not asking permission - I'm informing you so we don't work at cross-purposes. If you want to coordinate, move F RUM to support me into GRE or simply stay out of AEG. In exchange, I will stay entirely out of EAS and SMY - the eastern Med is yours. We can both grow: you push into Russia via SEV, I take GRE and we maintain the ION/AEG line. Agree?"}]
