ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Excellent - we are aligned. I will hold F BEL firmly to secure our position and deter any German move toward HOL. Your push with A BUR toward MUN is exactly the right pressure. I cannot support BUR-MUN directly from BEL, but my presence there pins German attention westward. F NWY moves to SWE to claim that center and threaten Germany's northern flank. Let's execute this coordinated squeeze - Germany cannot defend MUN, DEN, and their eastern positions simultaneously. After this fall, we should discuss dividing German centers between us."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I want to be direct with you: France is moving A BUR toward MUN this fall, and I cannot stop them from my current position. I'm taking SWE with F NWY - please don't contest it with F DEN as we'll only bounce again. I have no hostile intentions toward your core - BEL stays mine, DEN stays yours. If you want to coordinate a response to French aggression after this fall, I'm open to that conversation. But SWE is mine this season."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I must be honest with you: I am moving F NWY to SWE this fall. I need that center and the position it provides. I understand this conflicts with your plans for F BOT, and I apologize for the change - but my strategic position demands it. I offer you this: I have no interest in STP, FIN, or any Russian territory. Turkey's 5 centers are the real threat to you - F RUM and A BUL are pointed at your southern flank. Focus your energy there. I will not interfere with your northern expansion beyond SWE."}]
