AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy — your proposal to move F ION to GRE is a non-starter. I hold GRE with F GRE and I am not ceding it. What I will offer instead: I keep A BUD and A SER away from BOH and TYR this fall if you keep A BOH out of VIE and TRI. Your real expansion path is west against France or north against Germany — not into my Balkans. If you want to coordinate against Turkey, the move is F ION into AEG while I hold GRE and pressure BUL from SER. That gives you Aegean presence without stepping on my centers. Confirm A BOH stays north or west and we have a deal.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey — agreed on the anti-Italy framing, but I need specifics. This fall I intend: F GRE to AEG, A SER supports or pressures BUL, A BUD holds against RUM. If you hold F RUM and A BUL stable, I can move F GRE into AEG to threaten Italy's F ION from the east while you hold the Balkan line. That squeezes Italy out of the Ionian theater without either of us overextending. Russia is moving A ARM toward ANK — you should be aware they are positioning against you, not just consolidating. I am not joining that move. Confirm your F1902 orders and I will coordinate accordingly."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia — I hear you on Turkey's 5 centers, but F RUM on my border is as much my problem as yours. Here is what I can offer: I will not move on GAL this fall, keeping our border quiet, and I will not coordinate with Turkey against you. In return, I need A WAR to stay out of GAL and F RUM to hold — no Russian advance toward BUD. If you are genuinely pushing A ARM toward ANK, that is your business and I will not interfere. But I am not joining an anti-Turkey coalition this phase — I need one more season to consolidate GRE before I pick a southern fight. Neutral border, no coordination against each other — that is the deal I am offering."}]
