[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'The time has come to act decisively against Germany. I intend to move A BUR into MUN this season — Germany is weak and divided, and this is our moment. I ask that you hold BEL firmly to prevent any German retreat or reinforcement westward. If MUN falls, Germany collapses to 3 centers and we can divide the spoils. I will take MUN; you keep HOL and BEL. This is the coordinated strike we discussed. Confirm you will hold BEL and we proceed together.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Germany is the common threat. I am moving A BUR to MUN this season and I need your support. If you move A BOH to support my attack on MUN, we crack Germany open together. You gain leverage over Austria and I take MUN — we both benefit. Germany at 3 centers is no threat to either of us. Please confirm A BOH supports A BUR into MUN. This is the decisive moment.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'I will be direct with you: England is pressing me hard to attack MUN and is offering me significant concessions to do so. I have resisted thus far, but my patience has limits. If you want to preserve our non-aggression, I need a concrete gesture — move A RUH to BEL and demonstrate you are willing to act against England rather than sit idle. Otherwise I cannot hold back the pressure from London much longer. The choice is yours.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "The situation is clear: Germany sits at 4 centers with strong army positions threatening both of us. I intend to move F NWY to SWE this spring to secure that center, F HOL to NTH to dominate the northern seas, and A YOR holds. I need you to press hard on MUN with A BUR - if you take MUN, Germany collapses to 3 centers and we control the continent together. I'll hold HOL and BEL secure, keeping German armies pinned. What are your exact moves this turn? Let's coordinate precisely so we don't waste this opportunity."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I want to be straightforward with you: France is moving A BUR toward MUN and I cannot stop them from my position. I'm moving F NWY to SWE this turn - I need that center. I propose we avoid conflict between us: I won't threaten KIE or DEN if you focus your armies eastward against Russia. A SIL pushing into GAL or WAR would be far more valuable than contesting Scandinavia. Let's not fight each other while France and Russia circle. What are your intentions this spring?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I understand you're frustrated about SWE, but consider the bigger picture: Turkey has 6 centers and F SEV threatening your southern flank while A GAL presses from the west. I'm moving F NWY to SWE - I need it and I won't pretend otherwise. But I have no designs on STP or your northern territories. Your real threat is Turkey's expansion. I'd rather we maintain a working relationship than fight over Scandinavia while Turkey grows unchecked. What can we offer each other going forward?"}]
