TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Vienna, the situation is developing well for both of us. I see Italy has A BOH and F ION positioned aggressively - they clearly have ambitions in your territory. I propose we coordinate this spring: I will move A BUL toward GRE to threaten Italy's F ION from the north, while you hold GRE firmly. If Italy tries to take GRE, we can crush them between us. I need you to hold SER stable so I can maneuver freely. What are your intentions this season? Let's make sure we're not working at cross-purposes."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Moscow, I want to maintain our cold peace. My F SEV will move to BLA this season - purely defensive positioning, not threatening you. A ARM is noted near ANK; I trust you will honor your commitment to keep it away from my home centers. I have no designs on your northern territories. Let's keep the Black Sea region stable while the western powers tear each other apart. Confirm your intentions and we can formalize this arrangement."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Rome, Austria holds GRE with F GRE and A SER in support range - you cannot take it without significant cost. I suggest you redirect F ION toward the western Mediterranean where your real opportunities lie. I will maintain the AEG/ION non-aggression line as agreed. Austria is the growing threat here - they have 5 centers and are well-positioned. Perhaps we should discuss coordinating pressure on Austria rather than fighting over GRE, which benefits neither of us.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, the situation is clear: France sits in BUR threatening MUN, Italy occupied BOH last year threatening from the east, and you hold HOL which should rightfully be German. I propose we coordinate properly this season. I intend to move A RUH into BUR to push France back, and F DEN toward SWE. If you support my move into BUR or at minimum hold HOL steady, I will not contest BEL this season. France is the common enemy here - they have 5 centers and are positioned to dominate the west. Let's discuss specific coordination."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I must be direct with you: last season was a disaster for both of us with the MUN bounces. I moved SIL to BOH - not to attack you, but because I needed to secure my eastern flank against Russia. I propose genuine coordination now: I will support you from BOH into GAL or VIE if you move your BOH army south toward Austria. Germany has no interest in Italian home centers. Austria is the target we should both be pressuring. What specific move are you planning from BOH this season?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the SWE situation has been a three-way stalemate long enough. I propose we resolve it: I will move F DEN to SWE this season. In exchange, I offer you a free hand in the east - I have no designs on WAR or GAL, and I will not support Austrian moves against you. Turkey is growing dangerously with 6 centers including SEV - that should concern you far more than SWE. Let me take SWE and focus your F BOT on containing Turkey's northern ambitions. A coordinated German-Russian understanding benefits us both against the real threats."}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, my F ION bounced off GRE last fall - I know you hold it firmly with SER support. I'm not interested in a prolonged fight over Greece. Let's discuss a division of the Balkans: you keep GRE and SER, I focus on the eastern Mediterranean against Turkey. Turkey now holds SEV and is growing dangerously - F SEV threatens the Black Sea and their army in BUL is positioned to expand. I propose we coordinate: I move F ION toward AEG to pressure Turkey's flank, while you hold your Balkan position. In return, I need assurance you won't push into TRI or ADR. What are your thoughts on a joint anti-Turkish arrangement?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, you've grown impressively - SEV, BUL, RUM, plus your home centers. That's six supply centers and you're positioned to dominate the Black Sea. I want to be direct: I have F ION and I could move toward AEG, but I'd rather we find an arrangement. Austria holds GRE and is my primary concern right now. If you're willing to coordinate against Austria - specifically, can A BUL pressure GRE from the north while I approach from ION? - we could split the Balkans between us and both grow at Austria's expense. What do you say?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, you hold GAL with A GAL and I have A BOH - we're neighbors in Central Europe. Austria sits between us with BUD and VIE. I'm considering moves that pressure Austria from the south and west. If you're interested in coordinating against Austria, A GAL-BUD would be devastating combined with pressure from my direction. Turkey is also growing rapidly with SEV - that should concern you more than it concerns me. I'm open to a broader arrangement. What are your intentions this spring?"}]
