AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, the board position is clear: you sit at 6 centers, the strongest power on the board. I held GRE against Italy's F ION attack last fall — that was the right call for both of us. This spring I need to move aggressively against Italy before they consolidate further. My proposal: I push A SER toward BUL with your support, or alternatively we coordinate F GRE into AEG while you hold BUL firm. I am not moving on RUM — that is yours. What I need from you is a clear statement of your S1903 intentions so we do not collide. If you are willing to cede BUL to me in exchange for a firm anti-Italy axis and my support for your northern expansion into RUM/SEV consolidation, I am open to that conversation. Be specific about what you want this turn."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, Italy has A BOH sitting on your doorstep as much as mine — A SIL and A BOH together threaten both of us. I am holding my Balkan position this spring and not contesting GAL. What I need to know: is A GAL moving toward RUM, VIE, or BOH? If you push A GAL into BOH to dislodge Italy's army, I will support that move from BUD. That is a concrete offer. In return I ask you hold A GAL out of RUM — Turkey already occupies it and a RUS-TUR collision there benefits neither of us. Tell me your intended moves and I will coordinate accordingly."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your F ION is sitting in my backyard and A BOH is adjacent to my home centers. I stopped your GRE grab last fall and I will do it again if necessary. However, I have no interest in a grinding war with you when Turkey sits at 6 centers and is the real threat to both of us. Here is my offer: pull F ION south toward TUN or east toward AEG away from GRE, and I will not move on VEN or TYR this spring. We can coordinate against Turkey in the Aegean — F GRE and F ION together can threaten CON and SMY. If you continue pressing GRE, I will coordinate with Russia to dislodge A BOH and you will lose ground in the north while gaining nothing in the south. Your choice.'}]
