[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Confirmed - I will hold BEL firmly and move F HOL to NTH to dominate the northern seas and cut off any German naval response. You take MUN with A BUR, I secure the north. This is the coordinated strike that breaks Germany. After MUN falls, we discuss dividing GER's remaining centers - I want DEN and KIE via naval pressure, you can have MUN and BER via land. Let's execute this precisely."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I've heard your proposal but France is already committed to MUN and I cannot stop them - nor will I. You're asking me to support A RUH into BUR while France has 5 centers and is moving aggressively. My advice: pull A SIL back to defend MUN, and consider that your real salvation is a deal with Italy or Russia, not England. I'm moving F HOL to NTH this turn - not threatening you, just repositioning. I won't contest BEL or KIE if you focus east."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I'm taking SWE this turn - that's final. But I recognize Turkey is your existential threat with 6 centers and F SEV. I propose this: after I secure SWE, I have no further northern ambitions. STP is yours, Finland is yours. Focus everything south against Turkey. If you want, I can pressure GER's DEN from NTH next season to free up your Baltic fleet for the south. That's a better deal than fighting me over SWE while Turkey devours your southern centers."}]
