[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I accept your offer. A GAL will move to BOH to dislodge Italy's army - please support this move from BUD (A BUD S A GAL - BOH). This removes the Italian threat from your doorstep and gives us both breathing room. I will hold A GAL out of RUM as requested. In return, I expect AUT to remain out of GAL and to coordinate with me on future moves against Italy. Let us execute this together: A GAL - BOH, supported by A BUD."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I have received offers from multiple powers to coordinate against you in BOH. I am not your enemy and prefer to keep options open - but A BOH sitting adjacent to GAL and threatening Central Europe makes others nervous. I suggest you consider withdrawing A BOH to a less provocative position this season. If you do, I will not move against you and we can discuss longer-term coordination. The choice is yours.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I acknowledge your message. A ARM will not move to ANK this season - cold peace holds on my end. However, I must be honest: Russia at 3 centers cannot survive long-term without growth. I need SWE or a Balkan center. If you are willing to let me take RUM in exchange for a formal non-aggression pact and coordination against AUT, I am open to that arrangement. Otherwise I must find growth elsewhere. F SEV moving to BLA is noted - I trust this is purely defensive as you say.'}]
