[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I accept your proposal. F ION will move to AEG this spring, not toward GRE - I'm redirecting my eastern ambitions toward Turkey's flank. A BOH will move toward MUN or TYR, away from VIE. Turkey at 6 centers is the genuine threat and F GRE plus F AEG is a powerful combination against CON. Let's coordinate properly: you hold GRE and SER, I pressure from AEG, and we squeeze Turkey together. I expect you to honor your commitment to leave VEN and TYR untouched."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I'm moving A BOH toward VIE this spring - if you move A GAL to support or attack BUD simultaneously, we can crack Austria open together. Austria holds 5 centers and is well-positioned to dominate the Balkans if unchecked. I can pressure from BOH, you push from GAL. Turkey's growth in SEV should be your primary concern after we deal with Austria - I have no designs on your territory. Confirm if you'll coordinate A GAL-BUD this turn."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I cannot support BUR-MUN from BOH this turn as I need A BOH for a move toward VIE to pressure Austria - this is the bigger strategic opportunity. However, if you take MUN with A BUR unassisted and I take VIE, Germany collapses entirely and we both gain. I'm not blocking you, just pursuing a parallel attack. Let's both strike simultaneously and divide Germany and Austria between us."}]
