TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Rome, I am ready to coordinate against Austria. Here is my specific proposal: I will move A BUL to GRE this spring, threatening Austria's F GRE. You move F ION to support or press from the south. If we both commit, Austria cannot hold GRE against both of us. I will also move A CON toward BUL to support the advance. In return, I expect you to stay out of AEG - that is my sphere. Austria at 5 centers with GRE, SER, BUD, TRI, VIE is the dominant threat. Let's act now before they consolidate further. Confirm you will move F ION to support A BUL into GRE and we have a deal."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Vienna, I will be direct: I will not cede BUL - that is a non-starter. However, I have no intention of moving against you this season. My A BUL will hold, F SEV stays in the Black Sea, and A CON moves to SMY for repositioning. Italy is the threat - F ION is positioned against GRE and A BOH threatens your north. I suggest you hold GRE firmly and press A SER toward TRI or BUD to consolidate your home territory. I will not interfere with your operations against Italy. What I need from you is confirmation that A SER does not move toward BUL or RUM - those are my territories and any encroachment will be treated as aggression.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Moscow, your proposal to coordinate against Austria is interesting and I am open to it. However, I need a concrete gesture of good faith first: keep A ARM away from ANK this season - move it toward GAL or hold it in place. If you do that, I will consider moving A BUL toward SER to pressure Austria from the south while you push A GAL into BUD. We can divide the Balkans: you take BUD and WAR sphere, I take SER and GRE sphere. But I will not move against Austria while A ARM sits on my doorstep. Show me good faith and we can build something real.'}]
