[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I hear you on SWE - take it, I won't contest. My F DEN will move to SKA or hold. What I need from you is simple: stay out of KIE and DEN, and let me handle France. I am moving A RUH into BUR this season to push France back - this directly benefits you by relieving pressure on BEL. France is playing both of us against each other with their blackmail tactics. If you move F HOL to support my RUH into BUR, we eliminate the French threat in one stroke. Specific proposal: F HOL supports A RUH - BUR, I guarantee no German moves against HOL or BEL this season."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your ultimatum is noted but I reject the premise entirely. England is not pressuring you to attack MUN - that is a fabrication to extract concessions from me. I know England's actual position and they are focused on Scandinavia, not coordinating with you against Germany. If you move A BUR toward MUN, I will move A RUH into BUR and you will bounce, wasting your move while I consolidate. The smarter play for both of us is genuine non-aggression: hold BUR, I hold RUH, and we both focus on England who holds HOL, BEL, NWY, and is growing dangerously. Make the rational choice."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I am in BOH now and I propose we use this position constructively. Move your A BOH - I mean, coordinate with me: if you move toward VIE or TYR, I will support from BOH. Austria has 5 centers and is stable - they need to be pressured. I have no interest in fighting you; BOH was a defensive move against Russian pressure through GAL. Let us both profit: you take VIE or TRI, I support and then we divide Austria between us. Specific move: if you move A VEN - TYR, I can move A BOH - VIE with your support, or vice versa. What is your preferred approach?'}]
