GER
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "The situation in central Europe demands we coordinate. Italy has seized Vienna and Trieste - they are the rising threat to both of us. I propose we divide the spoils: I will push A SIL into WAR while you press south from BOH into Austria's remaining territories. In exchange, I offer you a free hand in Galicia and will not contest Warsaw long-term - I simply need to pass through to pressure Italy. Russia gains at Austria's expense, Germany gains at Italy's expense. This is the moment to act together before Italy consolidates. What say you?"}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, Italy has stabbed you badly - they sit in Vienna and Trieste while you hold only Budapest, Serbia, and Greece. I am prepared to help you recover. My A SIL can move to support your counterattack if you coordinate with me. I need you to hold firm in BUD and SER while I apply pressure from the north. Together we can push Italy back. What specific moves are you planning this fall? Let us coordinate precisely.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, France has consolidated dangerously - they hold BUR, PAR, and a fleet in ENG. They are a direct threat to both of us. I am moving to secure my eastern flank this turn. I propose we coordinate against France next spring: I push through BUR from MUN while you press from the channel. France must be contained before they grow further. For now, SWE remains contested - I suggest we let Russia have it and focus our combined strength westward. Agreed?'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, let's be direct. I hold VIE and TRI - your home centers are in my hands. I have no interest in a prolonged war that bleeds us both while Turkey grows to 6 centers. I propose a formal partition: I keep VIE and TRI as my gains, you keep BUD, SER, GRE. Together we can coordinate against the real threat - Turkey is at 6 centers and expanding. My F ION can move to AEG to pressure BUL while you hold GRE. If you fight me, Turkey wins. If we cooperate, we both survive and prosper. What say you?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, you sit at 6 centers - the largest power on the board. Everyone will soon turn against you. I offer a genuine partnership: my F ION moves to AEG to coordinate with you against Austria's F GRE, which we can take together. I want GRE, you keep BUL and RUM. In exchange, I stay out of EAS and CON. Austria is our common obstacle in the Balkans. Let's coordinate specifically: F ION-GRE with your A BUL supporting, or F ION-AEG while you move A BUL-GRE. Which do you prefer?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, you're at only 3 centers - we both need to expand aggressively. I'm pressing Austria hard from VIE and TRI. If you move A BOH toward GAL or support my position, we can carve up Austria between us. I'll take VIE and TRI permanently, you take BUD and SER. Austria cannot hold against both of us simultaneously. What moves are you planning this fall? Let's coordinate specifically so we don't waste this opportunity."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "The situation is clear - Austria holds GRE with F GRE and SER with A SER, while you sit in ION and I hold BUL. Last spring we both bounced trying to take GRE. This time let's coordinate properly: I will move A BUL to GRE with support from A CON moving to BUL (giving me a support chain), while you move F ION to support A BUL into GRE or threaten from the south. Austria cannot hold GRE against both of us. Confirm you will support A BUL - GRE with F ION S A BUL - GRE, and we split the Balkans with Austria eliminated from the south."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I want to be direct with you: Italy has A VIE and A TRI and is clearly coming for your home centers. I am not your enemy here - I will hold A BUL in place and not threaten GRE or SER. My concern is Russia's A ARM near my territory. I propose we both focus on our real threats: you deal with Italy pressing from the west, I deal with Russia from the north. A stable Balkan arrangement benefits us both while Italy dismantles your home centers. What do you need from me to coordinate against the Italian threat?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your position has weakened considerably - only 3 centers while Italy occupies VIE and BOH. I have no interest in pressing you further north; my concern is Austria and Italy fighting over the Balkans. Keep A ARM away from ANK and I will keep F BLA non-threatening toward SEV. We have a mutual interest in preventing either Austria or Italy from dominating the board. Let us maintain our cold peace while the western powers bleed each other.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'The spring results were frustrating - MUN bounced again and SWE eluded me once more. But the situation is clarifying nicely. France, I propose we finally coordinate a decisive strike this fall: I will move F NWY to SWE (securing that center at last) and F NTH can support or threaten DEN. Your A BUR should push hard into MUN - Germany is stretched thin with A SIL and A MUN both committed. If you take MUN, Germany drops to 3 centers and we can pick apart KIE and BER at leisure. I will not threaten your home centers - my focus is entirely on the Scandinavian/German theater. What are your specific intended moves this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I want to be direct with you: France has A BUR positioned against MUN and I have F NTH and F NWY in the north. I have no interest in destroying Germany entirely - a weakened but surviving Germany is more useful to me than a French-dominated continent. If you want to discuss a modus vivendi, I'm open to it. Specifically: if you can hold MUN against France, I will not press DEN this fall. But I need something concrete from you - what can you offer to keep English fleets from turning hostile toward your Baltic position?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I know we've had friction over Sweden, but let's be pragmatic. Turkey now holds 6 centers including SEV and BLA - they are the dominant power in the south and a direct threat to you. I have no designs on STP or your northern territories. My focus is SWE and German centers. If you redirect your energies south against Turkey rather than contesting SWE with me, we both gain more. I'm willing to formally acknowledge Russian primacy in the eastern Baltic (FIN, LVN) if you stop contesting SWE. What do you say?"}]
