AUT
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "The spring result is a disaster for both of us — Italy now holds VIE and TRI, two of my home centers, while Russia's A BOH is gone and replaced by ITA. We need to coordinate immediately. I propose: A BUD moves to either TRI or VIE to begin reclaiming my homes, and I need to know whether you can pressure ITA from the north. Specifically: can A SIL or any German unit be brought to bear on TYR or BOH to pin ITA? My F GRE is positioned in the Aegean theater but I can redirect A SER north. Tell me your intended moves so we can synchronize — ITA at 4 centers with VIE and TRI is an existential threat to me and a growing threat to you."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'You have taken VIE and TRI — my home centers. I will not pretend this is anything other than an act of war. However, I am a pragmatist: if you are willing to negotiate a settlement where you withdraw from one of those centers and we establish a clear demarcation line, I will consider it. If not, I will dedicate every unit I have to reclaiming them and will coordinate with Russia and Germany to ensure you face pressure on all fronts simultaneously. What are your terms, if any?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Italy has seized VIE and TRI — I am now fighting for survival in my own home territory. I need your assurance that you will not exploit my distraction by moving on SER or GRE. In exchange, I will not contest BUL or RUM this fall, and I am open to a formal non-aggression pact through 1904. A stable southern flank lets me focus north; a stable northern flank for you lets you consolidate your impressive position. Confirm your intentions.'}]
