RUS
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Our coordination last spring worked perfectly - A GAL moved to BOH and dislodged Italy. Now I hold BOH with A BOH and you hold VIE... wait, ITA holds VIE with A VIE. Let us continue pressing Italy. I propose: A BOH - VIE this fall to dislodge ITA's A VIE, and if you can support from BUD that would be decisive. Italy is sitting in your home centers - VIE and TRI both. We must push them out together. I will move A BOH - VIE; can you support with A BUD - VIE or A BUD S A BOH - VIE? Meanwhile F BOT will take SWE. What are your intentions against Italy this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'The cold peace between us has held and I intend to maintain it. A ARM will not move toward ANK - I am moving it to SEV to consolidate my southern position, which should not threaten you. My focus this fall is entirely on the west - pushing Italy out of Austrian home centers. I have no designs on BUL, RUM, or CON. Let us both grow in our respective directions without conflict.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'SWE remains contested between us and Germany. I am moving F BOT to SWE again this fall - if you move F NWY to SWE we bounce again and GER benefits from our stalemate. I propose you move F NWY to NTH or hold, letting me take SWE cleanly, and in return I will support your position against Germany in the north. GER has F DEN and A SIL - they are the common threat. Let us stop bouncing each other and coordinate against GER instead.'}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The bounce on MUN was frustrating but expected — Germany played defensively with RUH. The situation has changed: Italy now holds VIE and TRI, making them the dominant power in the south with 4 centers and growing. I propose we coordinate directly this fall: I will move A BUR to MUN (Germany is weakened with only 4 centers and their army in SIL is exposed), while you press from NTH toward DEN or BEL. If we crack Germany open now, we split their centers and neither of us falls behind Italy's pace. I need your F NTH to support pressure on DEN or threaten HOL to keep Germany from reinforcing MUN. Confirm your intentions."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your position is deteriorating — Italy holds VIE and TRI, Russia sits in BOH, and you are squeezed from all sides. I have no interest in destroying you if you are willing to work with me. Here is my offer: I will hold A BUR this season and not attack MUN if you move A SIL to support pressure on Russia in BOH, and we agree on a non-aggression line along the BUR-MUN border. Italy is the real threat to both of us. Think carefully — a France-Germany understanding is worth more to you than a hopeless defense on all fronts.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Congratulations on VIE and TRI — a stunning move. You are now the strongest power in the south. I want to ensure we do not end up in conflict. My focus remains on Germany and eventually England. I have no designs on your Italian home centers or your Balkan gains. In return, I ask that you keep your units east of the Alps and do not push into Tyrolia or toward Munich — that is my sphere. If we respect this division, we can both grow without friction. What are your intentions this fall?'}]
