[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Confirmed - let's execute this properly. I will move A BUL - GRE and A CON - BUL to maintain my support chain. You move F ION - GRE to support or threaten from the south. Austria's F GRE cannot hold against both of us pressing simultaneously. If you support A BUL - GRE with F ION S A BUL - GRE, we guarantee the capture. Austria is fighting for survival against you in VIE and TRI - their F GRE is isolated and vulnerable. Let's take it this turn."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I hear you and I respect your difficult position with Italy pressing VIE and TRI. I will hold A BUL in place and not move on SER or GRE - you have my word on that. Focus entirely on repelling Italy from your home centers. A stable Balkan arrangement is in both our interests while Italy threatens to eliminate you. I am not your enemy this season.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I appreciate the confirmation that A ARM moves to SEV rather than ANK - that is exactly the kind of good faith that maintains our cold peace. F BLA will remain non-threatening toward your position. We both benefit from watching Austria and Italy destroy each other in the west. Consolidate your southern position and I will consolidate mine - no conflict between us this season.'}]
