ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, confirmed: I am moving F NWY to SWE this fall to finally secure that center, and F NTH will be positioned to threaten DEN - this keeps German F DEN pinned and unable to reinforce MUN. Push A BUR hard into MUN; Germany cannot defend both MUN and DEN simultaneously with their current forces. If you take MUN, Germany falls to 3 centers and we can systematically dismantle KIE and BER in 1904. I will not touch BEL or threaten your positions. This is the decisive moment - let's crack Germany open together."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I appreciate the offer but France is already committed to MUN and I cannot stop that. What I can tell you is this: if you survive France's attack on MUN, I will not press DEN this fall - F NTH moves to support my SWE grab, not to threaten you. A surviving Germany is in my interest. Hold MUN if you can, and we can discuss a genuine anti-French arrangement in 1904 when Italy's growing power becomes everyone's problem."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I hear your proposal but I cannot yield SWE - it is too strategically vital. However, I offer this: move F BOT to FIN instead of SWE this fall, and I will take SWE cleanly without a bounce. In return, I formally acknowledge your primacy in FIN, LVN, and the eastern Baltic - I have no designs there. Turkey holds 6 centers and is your real existential threat. Let us stop wasting moves bouncing each other and both focus our energies productively - you south against Turkey, me west against Germany.'}]
