FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'Confirmed — my orders this fall: A BUR moves to MUN, A PAR moves to PIC to position for future pressure, F ENG holds or threatens BEL. Germany is exposed with SIL and MUN both needing defense. I need you to move F NTH to support pressure on DEN or threaten HOL so Germany cannot freely reinforce MUN from the north. If you take DEN and I take MUN, Germany collapses to 2 centers and we can divide KIE and BER next spring. Do not let this opportunity slip — commit F NTH toward DEN and F NWY to SWE as you planned.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I have received no response to my offer of non-aggression. I want you to know that England is pressing me hard to attack MUN this very turn, and I am resisting that pressure in hopes of a France-Germany understanding. But I cannot hold England off indefinitely without something concrete from you — move A SIL toward BOH to pressure Russia and signal your commitment to working with me rather than against me. If you do nothing, I will have no choice but to follow England's lead. The decision is yours."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I am moving A BUR to MUN this fall to crack Germany open — I expect you to stay out of Munich and respect the Alps as our dividing line. Your gains in VIE and TRI are impressive; focus your energy on Austria and the Balkans, where the real prizes lie. If we both grow in our respective spheres without stepping on each other, we can dominate the board. I will not move into Tyrolia or threaten your home centers — hold to the same standard and we have a durable understanding.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, we must act decisively this fall. I am moving A BOH - VIE to dislodge Italy's A VIE from your home center. I need you to support this with A BUD S A BOH - VIE - this is the critical move. If you instead move A BUD - VIE without support, we may bounce each other and Italy holds. Please confirm: A BUD supports A BOH - VIE. Meanwhile move A SER north if possible to pressure TRI. Italy cannot hold VIE and TRI against both of us if we coordinate properly. Confirm your orders so we do not waste this opportunity."}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I accept your offer - I will not contest SWE this fall. F BOT will move to a non-conflicting position. In return, I expect you to acknowledge Russian primacy in FIN and LVN as stated, and I want your commitment to pressure GER's F DEN from NTH. Turkey at 6 centers is indeed the greater threat to me, but I cannot fight south without first securing my northern flank. Let us formalize this: you take SWE, I take FIN next season, and we coordinate against GER together. Deal."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your proposal to push A SIL into WAR is a non-starter - WAR is a Russian home center and any move there means war between us. However, I am open to coordination against Italy. I will not interfere with your operations in MUN or TYR. Focus your energy westward against Italy and France; I will handle the Austrian theater from BOH. Do not move A SIL toward WAR or PRU - that is my red line.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Confirmed. I will order F ION S A BUL - GRE this fall. Austria's F GRE falls to your A BUL with my support. You take GRE, I reposition ION for future coordination. This is the move that breaks Austria in the south. Execute A BUL - GRE, A CON - BUL, F BLA holds or covers. I expect you to honor our division: you hold GRE, BUL, RUM, SEV; I expand through VIE, TRI, BUD. Do not move into AEG or ION - that is my water."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, my terms are simple: I keep VIE and TRI. In exchange, I will not attack BUD or SER, and I will support you diplomatically against Turkey's 6-center dominance. You retain a viable 3-center power (BUD, SER, GRE) and we establish a ceasefire line. If you coordinate Russia and Germany against me, you will spend your remaining units fighting me while Turkey swallows the Balkans - and you will still lose VIE and TRI. The pragmatic choice is to accept this partition and redirect your energy eastward. I am offering you survival. Reject this and I push for BUD next."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I am supporting Turkey's A BUL into GRE this fall to eliminate Austria's southern fleet. My A VIE holds and A TRI holds - I am consolidating. If you move A BOH toward GAL, we can coordinate a joint squeeze on Austria: I press from VIE toward BUD, you press from GAL toward BUD simultaneously. Austria cannot hold BUD against both of us. Confirm your intentions - are you moving A BOH to GAL this fall? Specific coordination now will pay dividends in the winter builds."}]
