AUT
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Confirmed: A BUD supports A BOH - VIE this fall. That is my firm order. You move A BOH - VIE, I support from BUD — VIE is dislodged. After that, I need A BOH to continue pressing toward TRI or hold VIE while I reclaim it. Do not stop at VIE — ITA has A TRI as well and F ION in the Adriatic theater. I am holding A SER in place to protect SER and GRE from any Turkish opportunism. F GRE holds or moves to AEG depending on Turkish behavior. This coordination is the only path that works — execute A BOH - VIE and I will support it.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I am coordinating with Russia to dislodge ITA from VIE this fall — A BOH - VIE supported by A BUD. I need you to pressure ITA's northern flank: A SIL toward BOH or TYR would pin any ITA unit that tries to reinforce. If you can move A MUN toward TYR simultaneously, ITA has no safe retreat and no reinforcement path. Tell me your exact intended moves so I can confirm the coordination is airtight. ITA at 4 centers with my home SCs is an existential threat — I will not negotiate a partition with them."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I am taking you at your word: A BUL holds, GRE and SER are not contested. My orders this fall are A BUD supports RUS into VIE, A SER holds, F GRE holds — I am not moving on BUL or RUM. The non-aggression through 1904 is accepted. Once I reclaim my home centers from Italy, we can discuss coordinated pressure on whoever is overextended at that point. Hold your position and we both benefit.'}]
