GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I accept your terms. I will hold MUN against France this fall - my A MUN stays firm and A SIL supports. In return, I ask you honor your commitment to leave DEN alone. I am not contesting SWE this season - F DEN holds. Next spring, let us coordinate a joint squeeze on France: I push through BUR from MUN while you press BEL and the channel. France with 5 centers is a greater threat to you than Germany at 4. I offer you this: I will not move into HOL or BEL if you commit to joint action against France in S1904. This is the deal that benefits us both.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I hear your offer and I am willing to consider it - but I need concrete proof of your intentions. Hold A BUR in place this fall as you promise, and I will hold A MUN in place as well. No attacks across the BUR-MUN line. However, I will not move A SIL to pressure Russia in BOH - that exposes my eastern flank dangerously. Instead, A SIL holds defensively. If you honor the ceasefire this fall, we can discuss genuine coordination against Italy in S1904. Italy in Vienna and Trieste threatens us both far more than our border dispute. Prove your good faith by holding BUR.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I want to be direct: I am moving A SIL to WAR this fall to pressure Italy's northern flank - this is not aggression against you, it is a transit move. I will not hold WAR permanently. Your A BOH is well-positioned to press south into Austrian territory. Italy is the common enemy - they hold VIE and TRI and will grow rapidly if unchecked. I propose: you take GAL and press toward BUD, I move through WAR toward the Italian-held territories. We divide Austria's remnants between us and then turn on Italy together. Respond with your intentions."}]
