ITA
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Excellent work last autumn - Austria's fleet in Greece is gone and we've both benefited. I now hold VIE and TRI, you hold GRE and BUL. I propose we continue coordinating against Austria: I will move A VIE-BUD this spring to take their last home center, and I ask that you move A BUL-SER to cut Austrian support and prevent A SER from interfering. With A TRI supporting A VIE-BUD, we can eliminate Austria entirely. In return, I confirm F ION stays out of AEG - the eastern Med is yours. Let's finish Austria together this season."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, you hold A BOH adjacent to my position. I propose we coordinate against Austria this spring: I will push A VIE-BUD with A TRI support, and I ask that A BOH moves to GAL or holds to prevent any Austrian counterplay. Austria is nearly finished - only BUD and SER remain. If we eliminate them together, we can discuss a fair partition of their remaining centers. I have no hostile intentions toward Russia - let's finish Austria and then negotiate a stable border."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I'm moving to eliminate Austria this spring - A VIE-BUD with A TRI support. The Balkans will be mine and Turkey's. I remain committed to the Alps as our dividing line - I have no interest in your western territories and expect the same courtesy. Germany is your natural rival in the west; I'll stay focused east. Let's maintain our understanding and both expand at the expense of weaker powers."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The situation has clarified considerably. France sits at 6 centers and is the dominant western power - they must be cut down. I propose we coordinate directly: I will move A MUN into BUR this spring while you press from the north with your NTH fleet toward BEL or the Channel. France cannot defend on two fronts simultaneously. I hold WAR and can threaten east if needed, but my priority is breaking France's western dominance. What can you commit to against France this spring? I need specifics - which units are you moving where?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I note you sit in BOH with only 3 centers while Italy has 6 and is positioned to dominate the south. I have A WAR which could move to MOS - but I have no interest in Russian territory. My interest is in coordinating against Italy, who threatens both of us. I propose: I move A WAR toward GAL to pressure the Italian position from the north, while you push from BOH toward VIE. Together we can strip Italy of their Austrian gains. What are your intentions this spring? I need to know if you're moving BOH toward VIE or elsewhere."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, Italy has stolen your home centers and must be expelled. I am positioned to help - A WAR can move to GAL to support pressure on BUD or VIE, and A MUN can threaten TYR. Russia in BOH is also positioned against Italy. I propose a coordinated three-way push: you hold BUD and SER while I move into GAL and threaten TYR, and Russia pushes BOH toward VIE. Italy cannot hold VIE and TRI against this pressure. Are you willing to coordinate? Tell me your planned moves.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "The situation has shifted dramatically since last season. France now holds BEL and occupies the English Channel with F ENG - I need clarity on your intentions. I'm willing to continue coordinating against Germany, but F ENG in the channel is a direct threat to my home centers. Here's my proposal: I move F NTH to DEN (taking it from Germany) and F NWY holds or moves to SWE, while you press Germany from BEL and BUR. In exchange, I need assurance that F ENG will not move against LON or support any hostile action toward England. Germany is the common enemy - let's finish them off together. What are your specific moves this season?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, your position is precarious - Italy has taken VIE and TRI, France holds BEL and threatens from BUR, and Russia sits in WAR and BOH. I'm willing to offer you a lifeline: I will NOT move F NTH to DEN this season if you move F DEN to SWE (giving me a clear path to SWE with F NWY) and commit A MUN to pushing back against either France or Russia. We can still salvage your position if we coordinate. What can you offer me in return for restraint on DEN?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the board has shifted significantly. Italy is dominant in Austria with 6 centers, Turkey has 6 centers and is growing - these are the real threats to both of us. I'm moving F NWY to SWE this season and F NTH to pressure DEN. I'd ask that F BOT not contest SWE - we agreed on this last season and it benefits us both to keep that arrangement. In return, I'll support your efforts to reclaim WAR from Germany. Let's coordinate: you push A BOH against Italy or A SEV against Turkey while I handle the north. What are your specific plans?"}]
