[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our coordination last fall was excellent - we both benefited from Austria's collapse. Now let's finish the job. I propose: I move A BUL to SER and A GRE supports, taking SER from Austria. You should push A VIE toward BUD to eliminate Austria entirely. Austria at 2 centers is nearly dead - let's divide the corpse cleanly. I take SER, you take BUD. Meanwhile F BLA moves to SEV to neutralize Russia's southern threat. This keeps our respective spheres clean and both of us growing. Agreed?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I want to maintain our cold peace. My fleet in BLA is not threatening you - I am focused entirely on finishing Austria in the Balkans. A BUL moves to SER, A GRE supports. I have no designs on SEV this season. However, I need you to keep A SEV away from RUM - that is my territory and any move there would force me to respond aggressively. Stay out of RUM and I stay out of SEV. Simple arrangement that benefits us both while Italy and I handle Austria.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, your situation is dire but not hopeless. Italy has seized your home centers and now threatens BUD. I am willing to offer you a lifeline: if you move A SER to support my A BUL holding in place, I will not attack SER this season and will instead pressure Italy from the south. We can coordinate to slow Italy's advance. However, if you refuse cooperation, I will be forced to take SER myself to prevent Italy from grabbing it. The choice is yours - work with me or lose everything to Italy."}]
