[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Confirmed - I will push A VIE-BUD supported by A TRI this spring. You take SER with A BUL-SER supported by A GRE. Austria is finished. F ION stays out of AEG as promised - the eastern Med is yours. After Austria is eliminated, let's discuss a clean border: I take BUD and the Danube line, you hold the Balkans south of SER. This is the moment to finish them."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I'm moving A VIE-BUD with A TRI support this spring to eliminate Austria. I ask that A BOH holds or moves to GAL to prevent any Austrian interference from the north. Turkey is taking SER simultaneously. Austria will be gone after this season - I propose BUD goes to Italy and we discuss a stable border along GAL/BOH afterward. No hostile intent toward Russia; let's coordinate to finish Austria cleanly."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, understood - I will not move toward MUN. A BOH is Russian-held anyway, not mine. My armies are focused entirely on BUD this spring. The Alps remain our dividing line and I have no interest in your western expansion. Take MUN and grow - we are natural partners with no conflicting interests. Let's both expand at the expense of weaker powers and avoid any friction between us."}]
