TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, we are aligned. My orders this spring: A BUL - SER, A GRE supports A BUL - SER. This cuts Austria completely and takes SER. You push A VIE - BUD with A TRI supporting - Austria is finished. Keep F ION out of AEG as agreed and we divide the Balkans cleanly: SER and BUD to you and me respectively. After Austria falls, we can discuss the Russian question - they are weak at 3 centers and ripe for partition. Execute your moves and I will execute mine.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, my moves this spring are focused entirely on Austria - A BUL to SER, A GRE supports. F BLA holds in place, no threat to SEV or RUM. I am honoring our cold peace completely. Once Austria is eliminated, I want to discuss a formal partition of the Balkans with you - there is room for both of us to grow at Italy's expense once Austria is gone. Keep A SEV away from RUM and we remain at peace."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I have considered your proposal but Italy's offer is more concrete and immediate. However, I will tell you this: if you move A SER to BUD to help defend against Italy's A VIE-BUD push, I will hold A BUL in place and not take SER this season. That is the best I can offer - defend BUD with A SER and I leave SER empty. The alternative is I take SER while Italy takes BUD and you are eliminated entirely. Choose wisely."}]
