[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, confirmed: I am ordering A BOH - VIE this spring. Please execute A BUD S A BOH - VIE. This is our best chance to dislodge Italy from your capital. Do not move A BUD anywhere else - the support is essential. If this succeeds, we can discuss how to handle SER and the broader Italian threat together. I am committed to this move.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I am moving A BOH - VIE this spring to strike Italy - not toward you. I ask that A WAR hold or move to SIL rather than threatening MOS. Italy at 6 centers is the board leader and must be cut down now. If you move A WAR toward GAL to pressure Italy's position, we can coordinate effectively. But if A WAR moves toward MOS, I will have no choice but to treat you as my primary enemy and abandon the Italian front entirely. Choose wisely - Italy benefits most from our conflict."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I am keeping A SEV in place this spring - no move toward RUM. Cold peace holds on my end. However, I note Italy has 6 centers and is the dominant power - they threaten everyone including you long-term. Focus on Austria if you wish, but do not let Italy consolidate unchallenged. F BOT moves north, A BOH attacks Italy in VIE. I have no designs on your territory this season.'}]
