[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I reject France's demand to cede MUN - that is capitulation, not diplomacy. Here is my concrete offer: F DEN holds in place this spring (no contest for SWE, you may take it freely with F NWY), A MUN moves to BUR to strike France directly, A WAR moves to SIL to consolidate my eastern position. I need you to move F NTH to support pressure on BEL or threaten the Channel to split France's attention. France at 6 centers is the board threat - help me hit BUR and we both benefit. Do NOT move on DEN or HOL and I will not contest your northern gains."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I will not return WAR - that is not negotiable. However, I offer you something more valuable: I am moving A WAR to SIL this spring, which removes any threat toward Moscow and positions me against Italy, not Russia. My A MUN moves to BUR against France. I have no units threatening you. Focus A BOH on VIE - Italy at 6 centers is the existential threat to both of us. If you attack me, Italy wins the game. If we both press Italy, we both survive and grow. Choose wisely.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, your ultimatum is noted and rejected. MUN will not be ceded. I have coordinated with England and Russia against you - England presses from the north, I strike BUR with A MUN, and Russia is free to ignore Italy and focus west. You cannot hold BEL, BUR, and PAR simultaneously against this pressure. However, if you wish to avoid destruction, there is an alternative: stand down from BUR, acknowledge the current line, and we discuss a genuine partition of England's holdings. Your choice - negotiate or be dismantled."}]
